node.text: Tests on Jets’ DE Carl Lawson revealed he suffered a season-ending torn Achilles, per source. Jets’ S Zane Lewis also tore his patella tendon and suffered a sprained MCL during today’s practice and will miss the 2021 season.

node.text: Bears’ HC Matt Nagy said OT Teven Jenkins is undergoing back surgery today, but “the goal is to get him back this season.” Bears hope that their rookie second-round pick can make it back in November, but there’s a real chance his season is over.

node.text: Detroit Lions announced they have released long snapper Don Muhlbach, who played 17 seasons and 260 games for the team, the second-most in team history behind only Jason Hanson. “Don Muhlbach will go down as one of the all-time Detroit Lions greats,” said Lions’ owner Shelia Ford Hamp. His release came on his 40th birthday.

node.text: 49ers cut Josh Rosen today. Since Arizona drafted him in the first round in 2018, Rosen has played for four NFL teams - the Cardinals, Dolphins, Buccaneers and 49ers. 49ers waived Rosen in order to claim CB Davontae Harris off waivers from the Baltimore Ravens.
